Today
**Junior Product Manager**
==========================

**Crop2Cash ltd**
-----------------

**Product \& Project Management**
---------------------------------

Ibadan \& Oyo State Full Time
Agriculture, Fishing \& Forestry NGN 75,000 \- 150,000
 Easy Apply
### **Job Summary**

We are looking for a Junior Product Manager who is passionate about building products that empower farmers. You will join a dynamic and fast\-paced environment and work with cross\-functional teams to design, build, and roll out products that deliver the company’s vision and strategy.


* Minimum Qualification : Degree
* Experience Level : Entry level
* Experience Length : 1 year
* Working Hours : Full Time
### **Job Description/Requirements**

**Responsibilities:**

* Researching, documenting, implementing, and managing software products;
* Testing and evaluating new products while creating product requirement documents;
* Identifying areas for modification in existing products and subsequently developing these modifications;
* Working with the Technology Team Lead to define product roadmap and vision, and execute strategies to achieve business goals;
* Defining functional specifications of the product(s) and managing the cross\-function group of people that would work on the project including engineers, designers, business development, sales, and marketing;
* Identify opportunities based on market needs, competition, and user requirements;
* Provide assistance to engineers and designers when needed;
* Work alongside the Technology Team Lead in managing and implementing sales and marketing targeted at users' activities through research, strategic planning, and implementation;
* Deploy software designs, tools, processes, and metrics;
* Maintaining and upgrading existing systems based on fixes required;
* Determine the root cause for the most complex software issues and develop practical, efficient, and permanent technical solutions;
* Remain current on new technologies and available vendor packages, evaluate and make recommendations as necessary;
* Assist in task planning, estimation, scheduling, staffing, and delegation of project/product tasks;
* Oversee skill/knowledge development through advice, coaching, and training opportunities as assigned;
* Determine process improvements, and best practices, and develop new processes;
* Work in close partnership with Team Leads, cross\-functional teams, and management;
* Reporting progress on projects to management using status meetings and other communication tools;
* Training users on how to use new and existing products;
Other relevant duties as may arise and may be assigned to the employee.  
* 

**Requirements:**

* Minimum bachelor's degree holder
* Proven work experience in product management
* Verbal \& Written Communications Skills
* Documentation and presentation skills
* Ability to manage all aspects of a successful product throughout its lifecycle
* Research and analytical skills
* Solid technical background with understanding and/or hands\-on experience in software development and web technologies
* Prioritization and time management skills.
* Worked with cross\-functional teams
* Interpersonal skill
* Leadership and personnel management

