Today
**Customer Onboarding Executive**
=================================

**Crop2Cash ltd**
-----------------

**Customer Service \& Support**
-------------------------------

Ibadan \& Oyo State Full Time
Agriculture, Fishing \& Forestry NGN 150,000 \- 250,000 Negotiable
 Easy Apply
### **Job Summary**

We are looking for an experienced Customer Onboarding Executive to provide excellent customer support to ensure users have an excellent first\-time experience and complete their registration. The goal is to ensure first\-time users have a swift and seamless registration and onboarding process, to increase customer satisfaction, loyalty, and retention


* Minimum Qualification : HND
* Experience Level : Entry level
* Experience Length : 2 years
* Working Hours : Full Time
### **Job Description/Requirements**

**Responsibilities:**

* Create and manage the team onboarding goals and expectations based on the duration of goals set;
* Manage a high\-volume, high\-velocity pipeline of leads from several channels to crush your quota;
* Build an effective onboarding process for onboarding and converting first\-time users;
* Formulating and revising customer onboarding policies and promoting their implementation;
* Assist in informing the team of all new information related to products, procedures, and trends;
* Manage and track onboarding inquiries resolution or brief the appropriate department to complete the inquiry;
* Build rapport with prospects from the initial conversation through successful activation of accounts, keeping all of your progress updated in the CRM;
* Assist Team Lead in communicating with the Product and Marketing Teams to collect feedback from first\-time users and determine the direction of Crop2Cash in Agriculture;
* Assist Team Lead in communicating with internal departments to provide an efficient workflow to handle both technical and merchants\-related issues;
* Delivering performance evaluations for all members of the team;
* Assist in building the budget of the customer support department;
* Collaborate with Team Lead to create and implement structures and standard documentation for the Customer Support team;
* Collaborate with HR for team recruitment and selection process;
Other relevant tasks as assigned to the employee.  
* 



**Requirements:**

* HND or B.Sc degree
* Previous experience in customer service, technical service, and other related fields
* Written and Oral Communication skills
* Documentation and Presentation skills
* Proficiency in Google WorkSpace, CRM, tools, and ClickUp.
* Team Collaboration and Delegation
* Prioritization and time management skills
* Ability to speak and understand multiple languages (Hausa, Yoruba, Igbo).
* Empathy and problem\-solving skills

2 days ago
**Sales Manager**
=================

**Crop2Cash ltd**
-----------------

**Sales**
---------

Ibadan \& Oyo State Full Time
Agriculture, Fishing \& Forestry NGN 400,000 \- 600,000 Negotiable
 Easy Apply
### **Job Summary**

Our Sales Manager is responsible for leading the planning, implementing, managing, and overseeing of the company's overall sales strategy for our existing services in collaboration with the management team. Your main responsibility will be to drive our business success by implementing a strong and sustainable sales strategy.


* Minimum Qualification : Degree
* Experience Level : Senior level
* Experience Length : 5 years
* Working Hours : Full Time
### **Job Description/Requirements**

**Responsibilities:**

* Drawing up effective and industry\-relevant sales strategies for national team activities in collaboration with the management team;
* Build a plan for locating prospects and leads for all our services across various platforms and geographies;
* Setting sales goals and developing sales strategies to attain the goals;
* Conduct market research to evaluate gaps, opportunities, and alien needs;
* Managing and overseeing the sales process and activities through specific in\-house software programs;
* Learning and understanding the details about our technology products and the services they offer users;
* Understanding all the prospect's needs, problems, or wants based on their various categories and locations across the country;
* Participating in conferences, exhibitions, programs, seminars, and training to meet with potential clients and act as their consultant;
* Up\-selling related relevant services to our users when appropriate and training the sales team to do so;
* Build and oversee the logistics network and activity for input delivery to customers across the various locations;
* Build and maintain input supplier relationships for purchasing and restocking products;
* Build an inventory management system and supervise the team’s frequent stock\-taking activities;
* Work in collaboration with the finance team to ensure the smooth running of the petty cash, sale invoice, and receipts system;
* Promote and retail input credit to smallholder farmers through visits to designated associations, cooperatives, and local government to support farmers' development by input financing;
* Ensure screening of prospective borrowers, including visiting their associations/cooperative meetings, completing the loan applications, analyzing the loan requests, and recommending disbursement;
* Through individual marketing and promotion channels, supervise the financing of new and repeated loans to increase the size of the farmer's portfolio;
* Monitor and leverage an adequate healthy caseload of active borrowers;
* Follows up on payments of performing portfolio to ensure adequate repayment rate;
* In coordination with the Sales team, follow up on payments of the bad portfolios from delinquent farmers to reduce its volume;
* Hire, build relationships, and manage the Direct Sales Agent (DSA) network;
* Preparing and documenting monthly customer and loan reports through authorized channel;
* Collaborate with the Customer Support Lead to identify and build personalized buyer persona profiles for all converting customers;
* Consult with the Growth and Marketing team to ensure the efficiency of the sales strategy;
* Identify the most important sales KPIs and track them for effective decision\-making;
* Document, prepare, and present sales reports to management on an ongoing basis;
* Stay up to date with the latest industry sales trends and best practices for conversion;
* Collaborate with HR to recruit, hire, and train new sales representatives.
Other relevant tasks as may be assigned from time to time.  
* 



**Requirements:**

* Over 5 years of working experience as a sales professional with expertise in closing product and service\-related sales
* Prior experience in the agriculture, technology, or fintech industry
* Self\-motivated and goal\-oriented, desire to deliver results
* Prior experience marketing alongside marketing and negotiating skills is a plus
* Experience working with cross\-functional teams and stakeholder management
* Proficiency in Google WorkSpace, CRM, and sales software programs.
* Available and able to travel when required
* Having bilingual skills is an added advantage (Yoruba, Hausa, Igbo)
